cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses caching content at geographically distributed servers and using cloud computing for dynamic allocation and release of resources. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses reducing wide-area network traffic and caching in content delivery systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses developing analytic caching models and optimizing parameter selections for cost/performance tradeoffs. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may discuss security concerns related to caching and content delivery systems. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper discusses optimizing cache performance and cost.
